APPENDIX 181

971. Ι prefer eam (A, etc.) to iam (BCP). Pampilus has been more worried about the identity of the bride than about the date of the wedding.

978. So Umpfenbach, Klotz, Meissner, Fleckeisen, following the η Mss. as closely as possible. There are so many parallels in Terence to the accent Gluce'rium that we need be at no pains to avoid it here.
